news.title: Hong Kong's CK Asset Holdings to divest property assets for $2.65 billion
news.para: CK Asset said on Wednesday its subsidiary would sell what it said was "the one and only issued share" in Aim Clever Holdings Limited, which indirectly owns assets such as 152 residential units in Hong Kong.

news.title: NCDRC admits class action suit against Omkar Realtors' subsidiary
news.para: About 56 homeowners of ‘Ananta’, one of the projects of Omkar Realtors had approached the consumer forum alleging that the developer has failed to provide amenities and facilities despite charging money for the same, at the time of selling the flats.

news.title: Chennai: Registration department can now cancel bogus documents
news.para: The department's order was handed over to her and four others by chief minister M K Stalin at the secretariat on Wednesday.

news.title: Magicbricks says searches of housing properties on its portal up 7% in Sept 2022
news.para: The average asking price increased 2 per cent compared with the June quarter, but searches and listings fell 2.9 per cent and 3.3 per cent, respectively.

news.title: Lokayukta overreached on Bagmane Developers complaint: Karnataka HC
news.para: ​The bench also ordered notice to the Lokayukta, the state government and Bagmane Developers Private Limited in a PIL filed by Samaj Parivarthana Samudaya, a Dharwad-based voluntary organisation.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Property tax relief for offices in factories
news.para: According to the modified rule, owners of factories which have office space up to 1,615 sq ft will pay property tax in the same slab as the rest of the factory premises.

news.title: Maharashtra government to soon list Mhada layouts for cluster redevelopment
news.para: Devendra Fadnavis announced that Mhada will be appointed as nodal agency for the redevelopment of Kamathipura and a cabinet decision will be taken soon.

news.title: Telangana: Fire norms for commercial buildings below 15 metres mooted
news.para: In the wake of recent fire accidents in the city, the state government has decided to bring in a new policy to make fire safety guidelines mandatory even for commercial buildings below 15 metres in height.

news.title: Finish Supertech twin towers debris removal from site by Nov 28: Noida Authority
news.para: It also directed Edifice Engineering, the company hired to demolish the twin towers, to construct a portion of boundary wall of ATS Village society which got damaged during the twin tower demolition on August 28.

news.title: Sebi lays guidelines on preferential issue, institutional placement for listed REIT, InvIT
news.para: ​The regulator has specified the manner of issuance of units under preferential issue as well as institutional placement by listed real estate investment trust (REIT) and infrastructure investment trust (InvIT), according to two separate circulars.

news.title: Maharashtra: 2,084 deemed conveyance proposals since June
news.para: Even as the department is pushing for deemed conveyance, of the 1.15 lakh cooperative housing societies in the state, 75,528 do not have conveyance deeds.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM inaugurates Ramco cement factory at Nandyal
news.para: The new cement factory with an annual capacity of 2 million tonnes of cement was established with an investment of Rs.1790 crore.

news.title: Continental Automotive buys 8.5 lakh sq. ft of office space in Bengaluru for Rs 850 crore
news.para: “Earlier, Continental occupied the same building on lease and now it has bought it from the builder. The building was leased for 15 years in 2022 with an option to buy,” said one of the two people aware of the deal.

news.title: West Bengal government extends rebate on stamp duty till March 2023
news.para: The West Bengal government is providing a 2 per cent reduction in stamp duty and a 10 per cent rebate in circle rate since 2021, a step taken to bring traction in the pandemic-hit economy.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment project to have four FSI, says deputy Maharashtra CM
news.para: The redevelopment authority will issue global tenders next week, said deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis. On Wednesday the housing department issued a detailed GR outlining the guidelines to be followed for the project.
